<dl id="hd11ydash"> <dt><a href="../../flex/h/hd11.htm">I.8&sect;1.11+'</a> </dt> <dd> A curious attempt at a late correction. On p.22 of <cite>transition</cite> 8 there is a marginal addition: &lsquo;Down to what made the potters fly into jagsthole.&rsquo;  Joyce appears to have thought it read &lsquo;Potters' River&rsquo; and wanted this changed into &lsquo;Potters' Rivier&rsquo;(p.22 &ldquo;Potters' River&rdquo; (see Letters, Buffalo, <a name="15Nov1927" href="../../FF/fbiog/fwlett.htm#15Nov1927">N.D. November</a> 1927). <ul><li>MS: Buffalo VI.H.2, fol. 1r </li><li>JJA 48 (Book I Chapter 8): 238 </li></ul> </dd> </dl>
